name: Delivery
title: Delivery
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contain codes commonly used in the outpatient setting to identify patients who had a procedure that would indicate they had a live birth or delivery.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is identify patients who had a procedure that would indicate they had a live birth or delivery.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element would map to the "Procedure, Performed" element.),(Inclusion Criteria: The codes used in this value set can be reasonably used to identify patients who had a procedure that would indicate they had a live birth or delivery.),(Exclusion Criteria: None)
